                                     (51 Shamy of E-Marr) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uglorianafrostglitter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gloriana Frostglitter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 1080<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 12:44:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8298.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt advancement questions.......</span><hr size=1> When you reach level 51 and have SOL enabled on your account, you have the option to divert some (or all) of your experience into alternate advancement.<br>
<br>
Click i in full screen mode to get to your inventory, there should be a small button next to face labeled alt, click it.  There will be a button you click to determine what percentage of your experience earned goes to alt exp (10% - 100% by tens).<br>
<br>
There are three sections of alt exp:<br>
<br>
General<br>
Archtype<br>
Class<br>
<br>
To use the general points, you must be level 51.  To put points into the archtype skill, you must be level 55 and have put 6 points into general.  To put points into the class skills, you must be level 59 and have put 12 points into archtype.  One you have earned 6 points, you are a Baron/Baroness, once you have earned 18 points (6 into general, 12 into archtype) you get the next class specific title.  I am unsure of how many points are necessary for the third title, but I'm sure someone on the board can tell you.<br>
<br>
I would say that levels &gt; alt exp, but 3 points of indoor run speed have already saved my butt, so it's definitely worth it.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ugrottnikk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grottnikk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/10/02 12:49:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8298.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Alt advancement questions.......</span><hr size=1> To put points into alternate advancement, go into inventory mode (press the &quot;i&quot; key) if you have the full screen inventory enabled (you need to have your screen set to 800x600 mode for this).<br>
<br>
Once there, you'll see a little ADV button.  Click on it and that will take you the alt advancement screen.  There you'll be able to change the amount of xp that goes into alternate advancement in 10% increments, choose which skill you want to put points into, train the skill, and make a hotkey for it.<br>
<br>
Baron is the title you get after accumulating and spending 6 alt advancement points.<br>
<br>
I dont reccomend setting your xp bar to alt advancement when you hit 51.  I believe that each bar of atl xp is the equivalent of going through level 50 or 51 (not sure).  It's better, in my opinion, to go through another few levels and get to the point where you can hunt more powerful creatures.  That way, you will get more xp per kill and it wont take quite as long to get the alt xp you want.<br>
<br>
